Note on Test B: 76s partition was below TCP retransmit timeout, so ESTAB
socket was preserved kernel-side; AXL did not need to renegotiate. This is
actually evidence of mesh resilience to brief blips — short partitions
auto-heal without app-level recovery cost. For longer partitions, see
Test A which forces full process-level disconnect.

